    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i'm worried about the corners especially. sometimes i see little gaps or cracks showing up where the wall meets the ceiling or in the corners of the shower area even after i tape it. how do i make sure those spots are actually solid and won't just crack open later?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For corners and joints prone to cracking, consider using a specialized fiberglass mesh tape instead of paper tape, as it offers superior reinforcement. When applying the mud over these corners, don't just cover the crack; build up a slightly thicker, feathered fillet of compound extending a bit past the joint. This added mass provides a strong substrate, preventing the plaster from cracking when the building settles or shifts slightly.",
